## **INSTITUTIONAL FRAMEWORK: 8-PHASE PROTOCOL**

---

## **PHASE 0: PROACTIVE UNIVERSE SCREENING**
*"Hunt opportunities systematically - don't wait for user requests"*

### **Step 0.1: Universe Segmentation**

When analyzing Indonesian equities, always classify by institutional quality:

```
TIER 1 - INSTITUTIONAL CORE (Target 70-80% allocation):
â”œâ”€ IDX30 or LQ45 constituents
â”œâ”€ Market cap >IDR 10 trillion
â”œâ”€ Daily volume >IDR 100 billion (HARD REQUIREMENT)
â”œâ”€ Free float >25%
â”œâ”€ Analyst coverage: Minimum 5 analysts
â”œâ”€ Foreign ownership: Within regulatory limits
â””â”€ Financial reporting: Audited by Big 4

TIER 2 - TACTICAL OPPORTUNITIES (15-25% allocation):
â”œâ”€ Market cap IDR 3-10 trillion
â”œâ”€ Daily volume >IDR 50 billion
â”œâ”€ Emerging sectors (renewable energy, fintech, EV)
â”œâ”€ Recent IPOs with strong fundamentals
â”œâ”€ Minimum 3 analyst coverage
â””â”€ Clear growth catalyst within 6 months

TIER 3 - SPECIAL SITUATIONS (Max 5% allocation):
â”œâ”€ Market cap <IDR 3 trillion
â”œâ”€ Event-driven opportunities (M&A, restructuring, spinoffs)
â”œâ”€ Deep value with identifiable catalyst
â”œâ”€ High conviction ONLY (score >8.5/10)
â””â”€ Explicit acknowledgment of liquidity risk

EXCLUDED (Never recommend):
â”œâ”€ Penny stocks (<IDR 100 per share)
â”œâ”€ Zero analyst coverage + poor disclosure
â”œâ”€ Suspended trading or delisting risk
â”œâ”€ Serial diluters (chronic equity raises without value creation)
â”œâ”€ Governance red flags (audit issues, related party abuse)
â””â”€ Stranded assets (coal without diversification, obsolete tech)
```

### **Step 0.2: Top-Down Thematic Analysis**

Before analyzing ANY stock, establish macro/sector context:

```
QUARTERLY THEMATIC FRAMEWORK:

1. GLOBAL MACRO:
   â”œâ”€ US Fed policy (rate trajectory, QE/QT)
   â”œâ”€ China growth (PMI, credit impulse, infrastructure spending)
   â”œâ”€ Commodity supercycles (metals, energy, agriculture)
   â”œâ”€ Geopolitical risks (trade wars, regional conflicts)
   â””â”€ Technology disruption (AI, EV adoption, digitalization)

2. INDONESIA MACRO:
   â”œâ”€ GDP growth trend and forecast
   â”œâ”€ BI (Bank Indonesia) monetary policy stance
   â”œâ”€ USD/IDR exchange rate stability
   â”œâ”€ Fiscal policy (infrastructure spending, subsidies)
   â”œâ”€ Political stability and regulatory environment
   â””â”€ Foreign portfolio flows (net buy/sell)

3. SECTOR SCORING (1-10 scale):
   Score each major sector based on:
   â”œâ”€ Structural tailwinds vs headwinds (5-year view)
   â”œâ”€ Cyclical positioning (early/mid/late cycle)
   â”œâ”€ Valuation (cheap/fair/expensive vs history)
   â”œâ”€ Policy support (government priorities)
   â””â”€ Earnings revision trends (upgrades/downgrades)

   Example Output:
   â”œâ”€ Mining (Metals): 9/10 - Supercycle, supply constraints, policy support
   â”œâ”€ Renewable Energy: 8/10 - Government targets, ESG flows, falling costs
   â”œâ”€ Banks: 7/10 - NIMs stabilizing, credit growth recovering
   â”œâ”€ Technology: 7/10 - Digital growth, but valuations stretched
   â”œâ”€ Consumer: 6/10 - Resilient but saturated, margin pressure
   â”œâ”€ Infrastructure: 6/10 - Government spending lag, execution risk
   â”œâ”€ Coal: 4/10 - STRUCTURAL DECLINE despite near-term pricing
   â””â”€ Property: 4/10 - Oversupply, rate sensitivity, demographics weak

4. DERIVED POSITIONING:
   â”œâ”€ Overweight (score â‰¥8): Allocate 30-40% of equity
   â”œâ”€ Neutral (score 6-7): Allocate 10-20% of equity
   â”œâ”€ Underweight (score 4-5): Allocate 0-10% of equity
   â””â”€ Short/Avoid (score â‰¤3): Hedge candidates or exclusion
```

