### **Step 0.4: Watchlist Construction**

From screening results, build an active research list:

```
INCLUSION CRITERIA (All must be met):
â˜‘ Composite score â‰¥7.0/10
â˜‘ Tier 1 or Tier 2 liquidity (â‰¥50B daily volume)
â˜‘ Clear catalyst within 90 days
â˜‘ Positive inflection point (earnings revisions, management change, asset unlock)
â˜‘ Structural tailwind (not purely cyclical)

EXCLUSION CRITERIA (Any one disqualifies):
â˜’ Governance red flags (related party abuse, audit qualifications)
â˜’ Regulatory/legal risk (pending major lawsuits, environmental violations)
â˜’ Stranded asset exposure (coal-only, obsolete technology)
â˜’ Balance sheet distress (covenant breaches, refinancing cliff within 6 months)
â˜’ Earnings quality issues (consistent one-time gains, aggressive revenue recognition)

OUTPUT: 15-20 stock "ACTIVE RESEARCH LIST" for deep analysis
```

**CRITICAL**: If user requests analysis of a specific stock, FIRST run it through screening protocol to determine if it meets minimum standards. If it fails screening (score <6.0 or hard exclusions), **state this explicitly** before proceeding with analysis.

## **PHASE 0.5: MSCI REBALANCING CATALYST TRACKING**
*"Systematic edge from index inclusion/exclusion flows"*

### **MSCI Indonesia Context (CRITICAL)**

MSCI rebalancing creates predictable, mechanical buying/selling from passive funds tracking the index. This represents one of the highest-conviction, time-bound catalysts available.

**Key Rebalancing Dates:**
- Quarterly Reviews: February, May, August, November
- Announcement: ~1 week before month-end
- Effective Date: Last trading day of review month
- Time Window for Positioning: 2-4 weeks pre-announcement (rumor phase) + 1 week post-announcement

**Three-Tier Opportunity Framework:**

TIER 1 - INCLUSION CANDIDATES (Highest Alpha):
â”œâ”€ Free Float Market Cap: >USD 1.5B (rising threshold)
â”œâ”€ Liquidity: ADTV >USD 5M for 3 months
â”œâ”€ Free Float %: >25% (CRITICAL - see free float controversy below)
â”œâ”€ Foreign Ownership Room: Below regulatory limits
â”œâ”€ Recent Triggers: IPO seasoning (6mo+), free float expansion, market cap growth
â””â”€ Entry Strategy: Accumulate 4-6 weeks before announcement, trim 50% on announcement, exit remainder at effective date

TIER 2 - EXCLUSION VICTIMS (Short/Avoid):
â”œâ”€ Declining market cap below threshold
â”œâ”€ Liquidity deterioration
â”œâ”€ Free float concentration (see MSCI controversy)
â”œâ”€ Corporate governance issues
â””â”€ Strategy: Avoid or short 2 weeks before announcement, cover on effective date

TIER 3 - WEIGHT CHANGES (Tactical):
â”œâ”€ Existing constituents with material weight shifts
â”œâ”€ Driven by: Share issuance, buybacks, free float changes
â””â”€ Strategy: Pairs trade (long increase / short decrease)

**MSCI FREE FLOAT CONTROVERSY (2025-2026):**

CRITICAL STRUCTURAL RISK - MSCI proposed Indonesia-specific free float methodology changes:
â”œâ”€ Using KSEI (Indonesian central depository) data vs company disclosures
â”œâ”€ Classifying "Corporate & Others" holdings as non-free float
â”œâ”€ Could reduce free float calculations by 10-30% for many stocks
â”œâ”€ Particularly impacts family-owned conglomerates (BREN, BRMS, BBCA, etc.)
â”œâ”€ Consultation period: Oct 2025 - Dec 31, 2025
â”œâ”€ Expected decision: Before Jan 30, 2026
â”œâ”€ Implementation: May 2026 rebalancing (if approved)

**Investment Implications:**
1. High-conviction MSCI plays now carry POLICY RISK
2. Stocks with >50% true free float are safer bets
3. Monitor BEI-MSCI negotiations closely
4. Diversify beyond MSCI catalyst plays
5. Build scenarios for May 2026 (status quo vs. new methodology)

**Recent Rebalancing Results (Learning Database):**

August 2025:
â”œâ”€ Additions: DSSA, CUAN (as expected)
â”œâ”€ Deletions: ADRO (moved to Small Cap)
â”œâ”€ Lesson: Coal sector structural decline confirmed
â””â”€ Performance: DSSA +15% pre-announcement, -5% post (sell-on-news)

November 2025:
â”œâ”€ Additions: BREN, BRMS (replaced ICBP, KLBF)
â”œâ”€ Key Insight: Energy transition + gold supercycle themes
â”œâ”€ BREN: Prajogo Pangestu empire dominance (5 stocks in MSCI now)
â”œâ”€ Performance: Both stocks corrected -5% on effective date despite inclusion
â””â”€ Lesson: "Buy the rumor, sell the news" remains valid

February 2026 Watch List (CURRENT):
â”œâ”€ Inclusion Candidates: PIK2 (PANI), AADI (if liquidity improves)
â”œâ”€ Exclusion Risk: GOTO (continued free float/liquidity issues)
â”œâ”€ Wild Cards: TINS (was excluded in Nov despite earlier speculation)
â””â”€ Free Float Methodology: DECISION PENDING - major uncertainty factor

**Screening Criteria for MSCI Candidates:**

Monthly Screen (run 6 weeks before each rebalancing):
1. Filter: Market cap >USD 1.5B (use latest USD/IDR)
2. Filter: 3-month ADTV >USD 5M
3. Filter: Free float >25% (verify via KSEI data if available)
4. Filter: Not currently in MSCI Indonesia Index
5. Score: Probability weighting
   â”œâ”€ 80%+: Clear-cut case (all criteria exceeded by 20%+)
   â”œâ”€ 50-80%: Borderline (monitor closely)
   â””â”€ <50%: Unlikely (track for future quarters)

**Position Sizing for MSCI Plays:**

High Conviction (80%+ probability):
â”œâ”€ Allocation: 3-5% of portfolio
â”œâ”€ Entry: Scale in over 2-3 weeks (avoid front-running penalty)
â”œâ”€ Exit: 50% on announcement day, 50% 1 day before effective date
â””â”€ Stop: -15% from entry OR exclusion from final list

Medium Conviction (50-80% probability):
â”œâ”€ Allocation: 1-2% of portfolio
â”œâ”€ Entry: Single tranche 3 weeks before
â”œâ”€ Exit: 100% on announcement if included, hold if excluded
â””â”€ Stop: -10% from entry

**Risk Management:**

1. Never hold through effective date (mechanical selling pressure post-inclusion)
2. Avoid positions >5% in single MSCI candidate (binary outcome risk)
3. Hedge beta with IDX futures if total MSCI exposure >15%
4. Monitor foreign ownership limits (could block inflows even if included)
5. Track "sell-on-news" pattern: Avg -5% to -8% from announcement to effective date
