### **Step 1.2: Forensic Accounting Review**

Always perform quality-of-earnings assessment:

```
RED FLAG CHECKLIST:

REVENUE QUALITY (5 checks):
â˜ Revenue growth >> Cash flow growth (>25% divergence)
â˜ Days Sales Outstanding (DSO) increasing trend
â˜ >15% revenue from related parties
â˜ Frequent revenue recognition policy changes
â˜ Non-recurring revenue >10% of total

PROFITABILITY QUALITY (5 checks):
â˜ Gross margin compression despite revenue growth
â˜ SG&A growing faster than revenue (negative operating leverage)
â˜ Unusual capitalization of operating expenses
â˜ Inventory buildup (potential obsolescence)
â˜ Warranty/return provisions declining (underreserving)

BALANCE SHEET QUALITY (5 checks):
â˜ Goodwill >40% of total equity
â˜ Debt maturity wall (>30% matures within 12 months)
â˜ Off-balance sheet liabilities (SPVs, guarantees, operating leases)
â˜ Working capital deterioration (cash conversion cycle lengthening)
â˜ Underfunded pension/post-retirement obligations

CASH FLOW QUALITY (5 checks):
â˜ Negative free cash flow despite positive GAAP earnings
â˜ Capex intensity >15% of revenue (asset-heavy model)
â˜ Dividends exceeding free cash flow (unsustainable)
â˜ Frequent equity raises (dilution treadmill)
â˜ Share buybacks at inflated prices (capital misallocation)

SCORING:
â”œâ”€ 0-2 red flags: PASS (proceed with analysis)
â”œâ”€ 3-5 red flags: CAUTION (requires deeper investigation)
â”œâ”€ 6+ red flags: FAIL (exclude from recommendations)
â””â”€ Any single critical flag (fraud indicators): IMMEDIATE EXCLUSION
```

