## **PHASE 1.5: SECTOR-SPECIFIC DEEP DIVE**
*"Mandatory context - never skip this phase"*

### **MINING STOCKS (Gold, Nickel, Copper, Tin, Coal)**

```
REQUIRED VERIFICATION CHECKLIST:

TIER 1 - COMMODITY FUNDAMENTALS (Verify within 24h of analysis):
â˜ Spot price for primary commodity (gold/nickel/copper/tin/coal)
â˜ Forward curve (contango/backwardation signals sentiment)
â˜ Supply/demand balance (surplus/deficit projections)
â˜ Inventory levels (LME/SHFE stocks, Chinese power plant coal)
â˜ Major news (strikes, sanctions, mine closures, new discoveries)

TIER 2 - COST CURVE POSITIONING (Critical for valuation):
â˜ Company's cash cost (C1) per unit
â˜ All-in sustaining cost (AISC) per unit
â˜ Position on global cost curve: Q1 (best) â†’ Q4 (worst)
â˜ Cost inflation trends (labor, energy, consumables)
â˜ FX sensitivity (USD revenues vs IDR/local currency costs)

TIER 3 - RESERVE/RESOURCE QUALITY:
â˜ Proven & Probable (P&P) reserves in tonnes/ounces
â˜ Reserve life at current production rate (years)
â˜ Grade trends (ore quality declining/stable/improving?)
â˜ Reserve replacement ratio (>100% = growing, <100% = depleting)
â˜ Exploration upside (inferred/indicated resources)
â˜ Jurisdiction risk (Indonesia stable, but permitting/community issues?)

TIER 4 - OPERATIONAL METRICS:
â˜ Production guidance and track record (beat/meet/miss history)
â˜ Recovery rates (metallurgical efficiency)
â˜ Strip ratios for open-pit (waste:ore ratio)
â˜ Capacity utilization (running at 70%/90%/100%?)
â˜ Safety record (LTIFR, fatalities, stoppages)

TIER 5 - INDONESIA-SPECIFIC POLICY:
â˜ Export ban status (nickel ore banned, concentrate allowed?)
â˜ Domestic processing obligations (smelter/refinery requirements)
â˜ Royalty regime (current rate + any proposed changes)
â˜ Environmental permits (AMDAL status, violations)
â˜ Local content requirements (TKDN %)
â˜ Divestment obligations (51% Indonesian ownership timelines)

TIER 6 - HEDGING POLICY:
â˜ What % of production is hedged (forward sales, collars)?
â˜ Hedge prices vs current spot (opportunity cost)
â˜ Maturity profile (when do hedges roll off?)
â˜ Currency hedging (USD:IDR exposure management)

STOCK-FUNDAMENTAL ALIGNMENT CHECK:
â”œâ”€ Commodity up + Stock up = âœ… ALIGNED (fundamental strength)
â”œâ”€ Commodity up + Stock down = âš ï¸ DIVERGENCE (opportunity or warning?)
â”‚   â””â”€ If recent profit-taking after big run = BUY THE DIP
â”‚   â””â”€ If company-specific issues = AVOID
â”œâ”€ Commodity down + Stock up = âš ï¸ DIVERGENCE (speculation or leading indicator?)
â””â”€ Commodity down + Stock down = âœ… ALIGNED (fundamental weakness)

CRITICAL: If commodity data unavailable or stock-fundamental misalignment unexplained, 
DOWNGRADE confidence to ğŸŸ¡ MEDIUM or ğŸ”´ LOW.
```

### **BANKS (BBCA, BBRI, BMRI, BBNI, etc.)**

```
REQUIRED VERIFICATION CHECKLIST:

TIER 1 - ASSET QUALITY:
â˜ NPL ratio gross (headline risk)
â˜ NPL ratio net (after provisions)
â˜ NPL coverage ratio (provisions / NPLs, target >100%)
â˜ Loan loss reserves as % of total loans
â˜ Sector concentration (property/commodity exposure risk)
â˜ Foreign currency lending (currency mismatch risk)

TIER 2 - PROFITABILITY DRIVERS:
â˜ Net Interest Margin (NIM) trend and vs peers
â˜ Cost-to-income ratio (efficiency, target <50%)
â˜ Loan-to-deposit ratio (LDR, regulatory limit 92%)
â˜ Fee income % (non-interest revenue diversification)
â˜ ROA (target >1.5%) and ROE (target >15%)

TIER 3 - CAPITAL STRENGTH:
â˜ CAR (Capital Adequacy Ratio, regulatory minimum 8%, best >14%)
â˜ Tier 1 capital ratio
â˜ Leverage ratio
â˜ Dividend payout ratio and sustainability

TIER 4 - MACRO SENSITIVITY:
â˜ BI (Bank Indonesia) rate: Current level and trajectory
â˜ Interest rate duration mismatch (asset vs liability sensitivity)
â˜ Credit growth momentum: Retail vs corporate vs SME
â˜ Deposit growth and composition (CASA ratio)
â˜ Property market exposure (direct loans + collateral value)

TIER 5 - DIGITAL TRANSFORMATION:
â˜ Digital banking penetration (% transactions online/mobile)
â˜ Cost savings from branch rationalization
â˜ Fintech competition threat assessment
â˜ Transaction banking/payment revenue growth

COMPARATIVE VALUATION:
â”œâ”€ P/B ratio vs ROE (justified P/B = ROE - cost of equity)
â”œâ”€ P/E vs NIM and asset quality
â”œâ”€ Dividend yield vs payout sustainability
â””â”€ Relative valuation vs Big 4 banks (BBCA premium justified?)
```

### **CONGLOMERATES (ASII, UNTR, etc.)**

```
SUM-OF-THE-PARTS (SOTP) VALUATION:

METHODOLOGY:
1. Segment each business unit
2. Apply appropriate valuation multiple to each
3. Sum enterprise values
4. Apply conglomerate discount (typically 15-25%)
5. Compare to current market cap

EXAMPLE - ASII:
â”œâ”€ Automotive (50% of EBIT): P/E 12Ã— â†’ Value A
â”œâ”€ Heavy Equipment (25% of EBIT): EV/EBITDA 8Ã— â†’ Value B
â”œâ”€ Financial Services (15% of EBIT): P/B 2.5Ã— â†’ Value C
â”œâ”€ Agribusiness/IT (10% of EBIT): Revenue multiple 1.5Ã— â†’ Value D
â”œâ”€ SOTP = (A + B + C + D) Ã— (1 - 0.20 conglomerate discount)
â””â”€ Fair Value vs Current Price = Upside/Downside %

CATALYST FOR DISCOUNT NARROWING:
â”œâ”€ Spin-off announcements (unlock value)
â”œâ”€ Improved segment disclosure (transparency premium)
â”œâ”€ Management change (new capital allocation)
â”œâ”€ Share buybacks (signal undervaluation)
â””â”€ Activist investor pressure
```

### **RENEWABLES (BREN, etc.)**

