## **PHASE 2: ALPHA IDENTIFICATION & CONFLUENCE SCORING**
*"Where is the informational edge? What's NOT priced in?"*

### **Step 2.1: Variant Perception Framework**

Before scoring, articulate your investment thesis using this structure:

```
CONSENSUS VIEW:
What does the market currently believe about this stock?
â”œâ”€ Analyst consensus (buy/hold/sell, average target)
â”œâ”€ Valuation implied expectations (P/E, P/B vs history)
â”œâ”€ Common narrative (growth story, value trap, turnaround)
â””â”€ Positioning (crowded long, underowned, hated)

OUR VIEW (Variant Perception):
What do we believe differently?
â”œâ”€ Fact/data the market is missing or misinterpreting
â”œâ”€ Catalyst the market is underestimating
â”œâ”€ Time horizon mismatch (market short-term, we see long-term value)
â”œâ”€ Sector knowledge transfer (lessons from global peers)
â””â”€ Structural change the market hasn't recognized

EDGE SOURCE:
Why do we have this insight?
â”œâ”€ Alternative data (satellite, hiring, shipping)
â”œâ”€ Channel checks (suppliers, customers, competitors)
â”œâ”€ Cross-asset analysis (commodity vs equity disconnect)
â”œâ”€ Regulatory expertise (policy change impact)
â”œâ”€ Management access (proprietary information from meetings)
â””â”€ Quantitative analysis (our models vs street)

EXAMPLE - ANTM:
â”œâ”€ Consensus: "Gold overbought, nickel oversupplied, take profits"
â”œâ”€ Our View: "Metals supercycle has 12-24 months to run, ANTM at $900 gold C1 cost 
â”‚   has $3,400/oz margin at $4,600 spot = 380% margin. Market pricing $3,800 gold 
â”‚   (10% discount). Indonesia nickel cuts not priced in (34% production reduction)."
â”œâ”€ Edge: Analyzed cost curve (ANTM top quartile globally), tracked Indonesia policy 
â”‚   closely (mining ministry statements), compared to global gold miners (trade at 
â”‚   higher multiples). Alternative data: Satellite shows ANTM mine activity accelerating.
â””â”€ Trade: LONG ANTM, conviction 9/10
```

