## **PHASE 5: CATALYST CALENDAR & EVENT-DRIVEN POSITIONING**
*"70% of alpha happens around catalysts - position accordingly"*

### **90-Day Rolling Calendar**

Maintain and update this weekly:

```
CATALYST TRACKING MATRIX:

[MONTH 1 - Current Month]
Day X: Event Name (Company/Index)
â”œâ”€ Type: Earnings / Policy / M&A / Rebalancing / Macro
â”œâ”€ Impact: HIGH / MEDIUM / LOW
â”œâ”€ Affected Stocks: [Ticker list]
â”œâ”€ Expected Outcome: [Bull/Base/Bear scenario]
â”œâ”€ Positioning: [Enter 2 weeks before / Trim before / Hold through]
â””â”€ Post-Event Action: [Take profits / Add / Exit]

Example:
Jan 27: ANTM Q4 Earnings
â”œâ”€ Type: Earnings
â”œâ”€ Impact: HIGH (stock volatile around earnings)
â”œâ”€ Affected: ANTM (primary), MDKA/ADMR (sympathy)
â”œâ”€ Expected: BEAT (gold $4,635, nickel $18,700 strong)
â”œâ”€ Positioning: Entered Jan 14 (2 weeks before), hold through with tight stop
â”œâ”€ Post-Event: If beat+stock up â†’ trim 30%, if beat+stock down â†’ add 20%
â””â”€ Probabilities: 70% beat, 20% meet, 10% miss

[MONTH 2]
[MONTH 3]

PRIORITIZATION:
â”œâ”€ Category A (High Impact): Earnings of holdings, major policy decisions, index rebalancing
â”œâ”€ Category B (Medium Impact): Competitor earnings, secondary catalysts, sector conferences
â”œâ”€ Category C (Low Impact): Tangential events, low-probability rumors
â””â”€ Focus on Category A + B only
```

### **Pre/Post Event Positioning Matrix**

```
EARNINGS EXAMPLE:

T-14 days (2 weeks before):
â”œâ”€ Action: Begin building position if high conviction beat
â”œâ”€ Size: 50% of target allocation
â”œâ”€ Rationale: Early positioning before momentum builds
â”œâ”€ Risk: Wrong if unexpectedly miss, but stop loss protects

T-7 days (1 week before):
â”œâ”€ Action: Add remaining 50% if thesis intact
â”œâ”€ Size: Up to full allocation (8-10% for top conviction)
â”œâ”€ Rationale: Closer to event, can refine view with recent data
â”œâ”€ Risk: Less time value but higher conviction

T-2 days (Just before earnings):
â”œâ”€ Decision Point: Hold through or trim?
â”œâ”€ HOLD THROUGH IF:
â”‚   â”œâ”€ Extremely high conviction (>80% beat probability)
â”‚   â”œâ”€ Management has strong guidance record
â”‚   â”œâ”€ Sector data confirms positive surprise
â”‚   â””â”€ Valuation still reasonable (not priced in)
â”œâ”€ TRIM 30-50% IF:
â”‚   â”œâ”€ Moderate conviction (60-70% beat probability)
â”‚   â”œâ”€ Stock already run up >10% into earnings (some priced in)
â”‚   â”œâ”€ Valuation stretched
â”‚   â””â”€ De-risk by taking some profits
â””â”€ Advantage: Lock in gains, let rest run

T+0 (Event day - After announcement):
â”œâ”€ Beat + Stock Up >5%: TRIM 30-50% (take profits, momentum strong)
â”œâ”€ Beat + Stock Flat/Down: ADD 20-30% (market misunderstood, opportunity)
â”œâ”€ Meet + Stock Up: HOLD (in-line but positive momentum)
â”œâ”€ Meet + Stock Down: TRIM 30% (reduce risk, wait for stabilization)
â”œâ”€ Miss + Stock Down >8%: EXIT 100% (stop hit, thesis broken)
â””â”€ Miss + Stock Up: EXIT 100% (irrational reaction, will reverse)

T+7 days (Week after):
â”œâ”€ Reassess position based on guidance and trends
â”œâ”€ If beat was structural (not one-time): May add back
â”œâ”€ If miss has remedy (temporary issue): May average down
â””â”€ If neutral: Maintain reduced position, monitor

OTHER CATALYSTS:
â”œâ”€ Policy Decisions: Position 2-4 weeks before (if timing known)
â”œâ”€ M&A Rumors: Small position (2-3%) until confirmation
â”œâ”€ Index Rebalancing: Enter 1 week before effective date (front-run passives)
â”œâ”€ Product Launches: Position after launch success (reduce execution risk)
â””â”€ Management Changes: Wait 90 days to assess new direction
```

